TEXAS Voters and all voters, VOTE!!! VOTE!! VOTE!! Here are the Do’s and Don’ts for Texas voters, but all voters should do their research on voting in their state, come up with a voting plan, and VOTE. Your vote is your voice, and it matters! 🗳✅•

•

node.text: A piece with The Undefeated I did almost 2 years ago. It’s as true today as it was back then. The scars were worth it because I love to swim! Nothing and nobody was going to stand in my way. I encourage the younger generation to press on! Believe in yourself!  Believe in your dreams! I see you, and I know you can accomplish what others may perceive as the impossible! ❤️ @undefeatedespn

node.text:
Praise Him in advance. To God be the Glory! 
❤️Col 1:17🙏🏾

I know a caption doesn’t do my feelings justice, but I also don’t have all the words right now to truly encapsulate how I’m feeling about this year, but more importantly this past week. 

What I do know is that I’m thankful. Thankful for the overwhelming love and support that has surrounded me before, but also in the here and now. Thankful to so many of you for believing in me when I needed it the most. 

I’m proud. Proud of the person that I have become through this journey. Proud of my fight, grit, and courage to face my fears, but most importantly, proud to walk away with my head held high regardless of victory or defeat. 

Thank you God and thank you all! A battle is never fought alone! Thank you to my family, friends, coaches, teammates, doctors, trainers, Team Wasserman, sponsors and partners, old and new fans, and more… I am completely overwhelmed by all the love and support I have received. Tokyo here we come! 🇯🇵 

And to those who may be struggling or need encouragement in whatever place you are in life right now. Success isn’t in the victory. It’s in the fight you bring. Don’t let fear be your guide. Let faith show you the way, and always ALWAYS keep your head up! ⭐️ 

Lol. And I’m ready to finally get some sleep.
